                    "measure": "Feasibility of the intervention measured as the frequency (percentage) of enrolled participants that complete the VR-directed BGBT inpatient program",
                    "timeFrame": "3 days of treatment"
                }
            ],
            "secondaryOutcomes": [
                {
                    "measure": "Intervention acceptability based on qualitative data and collected from audio-recordings of semi-structured interview",
                    "description": "Patient acceptability will be evaluated through semi-structured interviews within 1 week of completion of the intervention to understand satisfaction, expectations, and experiences with the protocol, including perceived benefits or harms, and barriers to use.",
                    "timeFrame": "1 week (semi-structured interview within 1 week of completion of the intervention)"
                },
                {
                    "measure": "Acceptability using the System Usability Scale - patients",
                    "description": "This is a 10-item question scale that are answered from a range from strongly agree to strongly disagree. Scores range from 0 to 100 with a higher score indicating greater acceptability.",
                    "timeFrame": "Day 3 (post intervention)"
                },
                {
                    "measure": "Acceptability using the Treatment Acceptance and Adherence Scale- patients",
                    "description": "This is a 10-item question scale that have a range from disagree strongly- agree strongly.\n\nScores range from 10-70 with higher scores indication greater acceptability.",
                    "timeFrame": "Day 3 (post intervention)"
                }
            ]
        },
        "eligibilityModule": {
            "eligibilityCriteria": "Inclusion Criteria:\n\n* Patients with Inflammatory Bowel Disease and self-reported pain\n* Hospitalized for management of IBD (inpatient medicine services at Michigan Medicine)\n\nExclusion Criteria:\n\n* Patients that do not report pain\n* Anticipated length of hospital stay is less than 72 hours\n* Patients that have previously had a seizure, loss of awareness, or other symptoms linked to an epileptic condition\n* Patients with binocular vision loss\n* Patients with an uncontrolled cardiac condition such as an arrhythmia, coronary artery disease, or neurological/cerebrovascular disease.\n* Patients that are currently pregnant",
